  "title" : "Querying for CLOB attribute in JPA",
  "body" : "<p>I want to search for a value of the datatype CLOB in the database. The attribute in the entity looks as follows:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Column(name = \"FILE_NAME\")\n@Convert(converter = CryptoConverter.class)\n@Lob \nprivate String fileName;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Unfortunately I am not able to query like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Query query = entityManager.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM OracleDok o WHERE o.fileName = :fileName\", OracleDok.class);\nquery.setParameter(\"fileName\", hanaDok.getFileName());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will lead to the following exception:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Inconsistent datatypes: expected - got CLOB</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>A native query would work - but the value is encrypted so I cannot use the filtervalue to match it against the value in the database because I can't crypt it manually with the key the databaseentry was encrypted.</p>\n\n<p>How can I achieve this? Is there any way to set a parameter correctly?</p>\n"
}